ot;<!-- -->Victorious<!-- -->&quot;</p><div class=\"space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Origin:</span><span>Arabic</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Lucky Number:</span><span class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 rounded-full font-bold\">1</span></div></div></a></div></section><section class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 pb-16\"><h2 class=\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center\">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class=\"space-y-4\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-pink-100\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">What are the most popular Islamic girl names?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">The most popular Islamic girl names include Fatima, Aisha, Khadija, Maryam, Zainab, Amina, Hafsa, Safiyyah, Asiya, Noor, Zahra, Layla, Hana, Rania, Salma, Nadia, Amira, Huda, Sabreen, and Reem. These names have deep roots in Islamic history and Arabic tradition.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-pink-100\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">How do I choose an Islamic name for my baby girl?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">When choosing an Islamic name for your baby girl, consider the Arabic meaning, origin, and whether it has Quranic reference. Names with positive meanings like &#x27;Pure&#x27;, &#x27;Light&#x27;, &#x27;Merciful&#x27;, or &#x27;Beloved&#x27; are highly recommended in Islamic tradition.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-pink-100\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">What Islamic girl names mean &#x27;Light&#x27;?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">Several Islamic girl names carry the meaning &#x27;Light&#x27;, including Noor, Sana, and Munira. These names express radiance and divine blessings in Islamic tradition and are beloved choices among Muslim families.</p></div></div></section><section class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 pb-16\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center\">Explore More Names</h2><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4\"><a class=\"bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-500 to-teal-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all hover:-translate-y-1\" href=\"/islamic/boy-names\"><h3 class=\"font-bold text-lg mb-2\">Islamic Boy Names</h3><p class=\"text-emerald-100 text-sm\">Browse 216+ Muslim boy names</p></a><a class=\"bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-500 to-rose-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all hover:-translate-y-1\" href=\"/names/religion/islamic/1\"><h3 class=\"font-bold text-lg mb-2\">All Islamic Names</h3><p class=\"text-pink-100 text-sm\">Discover 25,000+ Islamic names</p></a><a class=\"bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-indigo-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all hover:-translate-y-1\" href=\"/christian/girl-names\"><h3 class=\"font-bold text-lg mb-2\">Christian Girl Names</h3><p class=\"text-blue-100 text-sm\">Find 100+ Biblical girl names</p></a><a class=\"bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500 to-pink-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-6 hover:shadow-xl transition-all hover:-translate-y-1\" href=\"/blog/how-to-choose-a-baby-name-in-islam\"><h3 class=\"font-bold text-lg mb-2\">Islamic Guide</h3><p class=\"text-purple-100 text-sm\">Expert naming guide</p></a></div></section></main><!--$--><!--/$--></div></div><footer class=\"border-t border-slate-200 bg-white\"><div class=\"mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8\"><div class=\"grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.3fr_1fr_1fr_1fr]\"><div><a class=\"flex items-center gap-3\" href=\"/\"><div class=\"grid h-11 w-11 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-slate-950 text-white\"><img alt=\"NameVerse logo\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"object-