girl-names#rania\",\"description\":\"Rania means \\\"Queen\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":24,\"name\":\"Salma\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#salma\",\"description\":\"Salma means \\\"Peaceful\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":25,\"name\":\"Nadia\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#nadia\",\"description\":\"Nadia means \\\"Caller\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":26,\"name\":\"Samira\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#samira\",\"description\":\"Samira means \\\"Companion\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":27,\"name\":\"Amira\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#amira\",\"description\":\"Amira means \\\"Princess\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":28,\"name\":\"Huda\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#huda\",\"description\":\"Huda means \\\"Guidance\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":29,\"name\":\"Sabreen\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#sabreen\",\"description\":\"Sabreen means \\\"Patient\\\" - Arabic origin\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":30,\"name\":\"Reem\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/islamic/girl-names#reem\",\"description\":\"Reem means \\\"White Gazelle\\\" - Arabic origin\"}]}},{\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the most popular Islamic girl names?\",\"answerCount\":1,\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The most popular Islamic girl names include Fatima, Aisha, Khadija, Maryam, Zainab, Amina, Hafsa, Safiyyah, Asiya, Noor, Zahra, Layla, Hana, Rania, Salma, Nadia, Amira, Huda, Sabreen, and Reem. These names have deep roots in Islamic history and Arabic tradition.\",\